 reproductive rate. Indications are that it also has a very small wild population which may", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "54eecce9-e0d0-4d25-97c3-2def1924deb6": {"__data__": {"id_": "54eecce9-e0d0-4d25-97c3-2def1924deb6", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.iucn.org/resources/grey-literature/iucntraffic-analyses-proposals-amend-cites-appendices-17th-meeting", "Author": "International Union for Conservation of Nature", "Publisher": "International Union for Conservation of Nature", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "IUCN/TRAFFIC analyses of the proposals to amend the CITES appendices at the 17th meeting of the Conference of the Parties", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.iucn.org/resources/grey-literature/iucntraffic-analyses-proposals-amend-cites-appendices-17th-meeting", "Author": "International Union for Conservation of Nature", "Publisher": "International Union for Conservation of Nature", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "289fe07d0cdcfe0c0c5ba9e605db063de9a4f3ddd0aaf1d6ea13ce65e6389e5c"}, "3": {"node_id": "b96ff0e4-3177-4eeb-aeac-6df1213f944c", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.iucn.org/resources/grey-literature/iucntraffic-analyses-proposals-amend-cites-appendices-17th-meeting", "Author": "International Union for Conservation of Nature", "Publisher": "International Union for Conservation of Nature", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "578fde0c7bb05a8c7a034a99643ca57240b35da4334c345f5b36cbaeb4c964dd"}}, "hash": "ac8d66e4197dd40152d36c0b646c6895f665736819d89d10cd960c76713e0325", "text": "be vulnerable to extrinsic factors including predation by introduced species and collection for export. It would appear therefore to meet the biological criteria for inclusion in Appendi